Notes We first define expressed genes in the Macrophages or T cells and NK cells (sender) and malignant cells (receiver). Genes are considered to be expressed within one cell type if their log2-transformed mean TPM (transcript per kilobase million) values are greater than 4, following the same criterion as in the NicheNet tutorial. The mean TPM value for each cell type is calculated based on the cell-type-specific gene expression of spots with the corresponding proportion greater than 0.05 within the focused spots.

lr_network <- readRDS("./realdata/LR_analysis/lr_network_human_21122021.rds")

## ligand-target matrix denoting regulatory potential scores between ligands and targets (ligands in columns)

ligand_target_matrix <-  readRDS("./realdata/LR_analysis/ligand_target_matrix_nsga2r_final.rds")

Notes: Filtering Expressed Genes

# Define genes and filter spots based on criteria
keep_genes <- rownames(stged$F_list$TSK)
keep_spots_Macro <- stged$beta[,"Macro"] > 0.05
keep_spots_Malignant <- stged$beta[,"TSK" ] > 0.05
keep_spots_T <- stged$beta[,"T and NK cells"] > 0.05

# Identify expressed genes for T cells, macrophages, and malignant cells
expressed_genes_T <- keep_genes[log2(rowMeans(stged$F_list[["T and NK cells"]][,keep_spots_T, 
                                                                                     drop = FALSE] * 1e6) + 1) >= 4]

expressed_genes_Macro <- keep_genes[log2(rowMeans(stged$F_list[["Macro"]][,keep_spots_Macro, drop = FALSE] * 1e6) + 1) >= 4]

expressed_genes_Malignant <- keep_genes[log2(rowMeans(stged$F_list[["TSK"]][,keep_spots_Malignant, drop = FALSE] * 1e6) + 1) >= 4]

Notes:The gene set of interest comprises the identified potential interaction-changed genes, encompassing both significantly positively correlated genes and significantly negatively correlated genes.

# Convert gene names and intersect with ligand-target matrix
geneset_ctHVG_macor <- intersect(convert_alias_to_symbols(toupper(Macrophages), "human", verbose = FALSE), colnames(ligand_target_matrix))

geneset_ctHVG_Tcell <- intersect(convert_alias_to_symbols(toupper(Tcells), "human", verbose = FALSE), colnames(ligand_target_matrix))

Notes:

# Convert gene names and intersect with ligand-target matrix
test_genes <- rownames(stged$F_list$TSK)[rowSums(stged$F_list$TSK) != 0]

background_expressed_genes <- intersect(convert_alias_to_symbols(toupper(test_genes), "human", verbose = FALSE), rownames(ligand_target_matrix))

Notes:The potential ligands are defined as ligands expressed in at least one immune cell type and for which at least one putative receptor is expressed in malignant cells.

# Identify ligands and receptors from the ligand-receptor network
ligands <- lr_network %>% pull(from) %>% unique()
expressed_ligands_T <- intersect(ligands, expressed_genes_T)
expressed_ligands_Macro <- intersect(ligands, expressed_genes_Macro)

receptors <- lr_network %>% pull(to) %>% unique()
expressed_receptors <- intersect(receptors, expressed_genes_Malignant)

# Identify potential ligands interacting with receptors
potential_ligands_T <- lr_network %>% filter(from %in% expressed_ligands_T & to %in% expressed_receptors) %>% pull(from) %>% unique()

potential_ligands_Macro <- lr_network %>% filter(from %in% expressed_ligands_Macro & to %in% expressed_receptors) %>% pull(from) %>% unique()

Notes:We then perform NicheNets ligand activity analysis.

# Predict ligand activities for macrophages
ligand_activities_macro <- predict_ligand_activities(
  geneset = geneset_ctHVG_macor, 
  background_expressed_genes = background_expressed_genes, 
  ligand_target_matrix = ligand_target_matrix, 
  potential_ligands = potential_ligands_Macro
)
